<div id="review_577870365" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/577870365" />
    <a title="Allison" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4579200-allison"><img alt="Allison" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1328890684p2/4579200.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/577870365?book_show_action=true">Apr 01, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Allison" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Allison" href="/user/show/4579200-allison">Allison</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer577870365" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1205682676303190607">I enjoyed this book, but left wanting more. It is clear that the author is not a writer, because she&apos;s constantly contradicting herself throughout the book...as often as saying something, and literally 2 pages later saying exactly the opposite. There are also loose ends everywhere..starts of stories that are never completed, random statements that are never fulfilled. If this is on purpose to showcase the mental tax of narcolepsy, brava; but I don&apos;t think that&apos;s the case. Much of this book is wr</span>
  <span id="freeText1205682676303190607" style="display:none">I enjoyed this book, but left wanting more. It is clear that the author is not a writer, because she's constantly contradicting herself throughout the book...as often as saying something, and literally 2 pages later saying exactly the opposite. There are also loose ends everywhere..starts of stories that are never completed, random statements that are never fulfilled. If this is on purpose to showcase the mental tax of narcolepsy, brava; but I don't think that's the case. Much of this book is written as an advice column: life is too short! Be happy in your career! It seems like the author wanted to believe that's how she was living her life, so she clobbers the reader over the head with these sentiments. However, reading through the book, it's clear that she wasn't taking her own advice.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1205682676303190607" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


