              <span id="reviewTextContainer650695346" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17831392507269208408">A very open and honest telling of a life changed by narcolepsy and cataplexy. Flygare explains her emotions and experiences from the onset of the disease through diagnosis, treatment, and learning to live with it. She admirably rises to the challenge and, while not the life she&apos;d imagined for herself, finds her place in the world. Reading this memoire helped me better understand what my niece has experienced - I&apos;m so proud of you, Teresa!</span>
